    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PRACH thread busy detection logic\n\n### Summary\nThe eNB PRACH processing threads were incorrectly dropping PRACH opportunities due to a logic error in the busy detection checks. Under normal operating conditions, this caused random PRACH detection failures and UE attachment timeouts.\n\nThe issue was in the condition checks that determine when to drop incoming PRACH requests. The code was checking `instance_cnt_prach == 0` which indicates the thread has been signaled but hasn't started processing yet, not when it's actually busy.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Changed busy detection from `== 0` to `> 0` for both PRACH threads\n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Fixed wakeup_prach_eNB function  \n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Fixed wakeup_prach_eNB_br function\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure eNB with PRACH enabled\n2. Connect multiple UEs attempting RACH simultaneously \n3. Observe PRACH detection failures in logs with messages like \"[eNB] Frame X Subframe Y, dropping PRACH\"\n4. UEs experience random RACH timeouts and attachment failures\n\nThe fix ensures PRACH requests are only dropped when the processing thread is actually busy (instance count > 0) rather than when it's simply been signaled to start processing.\n"
}